Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick.

Crack the @Egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @Breadcrumbs{50%grams} into another medium bowl, mix and season with the @Salt for the Breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{for frying} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a large baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, carefully discard the oil from the #chicken pan{}. Wipe it out and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{for cooking}.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Spring Greens{150%grams} along with the @water{for cooking}, cover with a tight-fitting #lid{} and cook until wilted, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the spring greens cook, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, sprinkle over half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}, then return to the oven for the remaining time.

When the schnitzel is cooked, sprinkle over the remaining cheese. Cover to keep warm.

When the spring greens have softened, stir in the garlic, @Honey{15%grams}, @Butter{20%grams} and @Wholegrain Mustard{8.5%grams}. Fry, ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Share the chicken schnitzels between your #plates{}.

Serve the roasted potatoes and spring greens alongside.

Serve with the @Redcurrant Jelly{37%grams} and @Mayonnaise{3%tbsp} for dipping.

Enjoy!